HEADWORD: Njorth
<hw>Njorth</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Teutonic
mythology)</fld> <def>Chief of the Vanir; god of the sea and winds and
prosperity; father of <persfn>Frey</persfn> and <persfn>Freya</persfn>;
sometimes subsumes Teutonic Nerthus.</def>⟦br⟧
